<p id="mwAo4">After quantization, replacing the position vector <i id="mwAo8">x</i> with a <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Wave_function" title="Wave function" id="mwApA">wave function</a>, the parameter <i id="mwApE">m</i> appears in the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Kinetic_energy" title="Kinetic energy" id="mwApI">kinetic energy</a> operator:</p>
<dl id="mwApM"><dd id="mwApQ"><span class="mwe-math-element" typeof="mw:Extension/math" about="#mwt421" data-mw='{"name":"math","attrs":{},"body":{"extsrc":"i\\hbar\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial t} \\Psi(\\mathbf{r},\\,t) =  \\left(-\\frac{\\hbar^2}{2m}\\nabla^2 + V(\\mathbf{r})\\right)\\Psi(\\mathbf{r},\\,t)"}}' id="mwApU"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle i\hbar {\frac {\partial }{\partial t}}\Psi (\mathbf {r} ,\,t)=\left(-{\frac {\hbar ^{2}}{2m}}\nabla ^{2}+V(\mathbf {r} )\right)\Psi (\mathbf {r} ,\,t)}">
